    {
      "section_id": "601",
      "section_title": "Emission Tests",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "11-5-2REGULATION 11 HAZARDOUS POLLUTANTS MERCURY"
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "100",
      "section_title": "GENERAL",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "101",
      "section_title": "Description",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "The purpose of this Rule is to control the emission of mercury to the atmosphere."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "200",
      "section_title": "DEFINITIONS",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "201",
      "section_title": "Condenser Stack Gases",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "The gaseous effluent emitted from the stack or processes utilizing heat to extract mercury metal from mercury ore."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "202",
      "section_title": "Hydrogen Gas Steam",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "A device which is basically composed of an electrolyzer section and a denuder (decomposer) section and utilizes mercury to produce chlorine gas, hydrogen gas and alkali metal hydroxide."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "300",
      "section_title": "STANDARDS",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "301",
      "section_title": "Discharges From Plants Processing Mercury Ore",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "A person shall not discharge from plants or operations which process mercury ore, and which use mercury chloralkali cells, more than 2.3 kg of mercury per 24 hour period. Such weight shall include mercury as particulates, vapors, aerosols, and compounds.",
        "Such weights or concentrations apply to the element mercury only, excluding the weight or concentration of any associated elements."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "302",
      "section_title": "Discharges From Sludge Incineration Plants",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "A person shall not discharge from sludge incineration plants, sludge drying plants or a combination of these that process wastewater treatment plant sludges, more than 3.2 kg of mercury per 24 hour period."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "400",
      "section_title": "ADMINISTRAT IVE PROCEDURES",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "401",
      "section_title": "Testing",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "Unless a waiver of emission testing has been obtained from the APCO, a person subject to the emission limits of this Rule shall test emissions from the plant within 90 days of any startup of a new source operation."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "402",
      "section_title": "Reporting",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "The APCO shall be notified at least 30 days prior to an emission test, in order that the APCO have the option to conduct or observe the test."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "600",
      "section_title": "MANUAL OF P ROCEDURES",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "601",
      "section_title": "Emission Tests",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "Any person required to make an emission test shall use test methods and procedures as specified in the Manual of Procedures."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    }
